# Sureops-owned: chart, agent contract, internal docs, CI workflows.
# Customer can PR these but sureops staff must approve before merge.
/chart/                 @sureops-private-beta/sureops-staff
/.sureops/              @sureops-private-beta/sureops-staff
/.sureops-internal/     @sureops-private-beta/sureops-staff
/.github/workflows/     @sureops-private-beta/sureops-staff
/.github/CODEOWNERS     @sureops-private-beta/sureops-staff

# Customer-owned: source code. Customer's team is the implicit owner;
# they can merge PRs against src/ without sureops approval.
# (No CODEOWNERS line for /src/ — defaults to "anyone with write access can merge".)

# Docs: shared. Both sureops staff and customer can edit.
/docs/                  @sureops-private-beta/sureops-staff
README.md               @sureops-private-beta/sureops-staff
